## Errors & Mistakes
- BIGGEST SEMANTIC GOTCHA: SQLite column AFFINITY. First failure was
  test_calls_query_stats_started_at_window_excludes_deletes:
  started_at > 99999999999 must return 0 rows because the no-affinity
  numeric literal is converted to TEXT ('99999999999' > '2026-...').
  Storage-class ordering alone (numeric < text) returns ALL rows. Fixed
  with _apply_comparison_affinity + _CALLS_INTEGER_COLUMNS; applies to
  binary ops AND $in elements.
- Filter length validation (assert_parameter_length_less_than_max) was
  initially inside the per-record matcher, so it never fired on an empty
  store; test_calls_query_hardcoded_filter_length_validation expects the
  ValueError with zero rows. Hoisted to _validate_calls_filter run once.
- feedback_query(fields=["count(*)"]) crashed: the ORM treats count(*) as
  a valid field; added an aggregate branch (count over pre-LIMIT matched
  rows; LIMIT/OFFSET apply to the single result row).
- First perf benchmark showed queries 2.5x SLOWER than sqlite and tables
  1.7x slower: per-record AST interpretation rebuilt closures 15k times,
  and copy.deepcopy dominated. Fixes: compile-once query/sort closures,
  _json_deep_copy (plain-JSON recursion), and table_query now sorts/slices
  on raw (index, digest, val) tuples and materializes pydantic rows only
  for the returned slice. After: queries 1.4x, objects 4.3x, tables 3.0x,
  writes 1.6x FASTER than sqlite; costs section at parity (the bench's
  0.3x readout there is one-time seeding + measurement-order artifact;
  isolated timing showed 6.6ms cold / 3ms warm vs sqlite 8-10ms).
- A scripted bulk edit failed with "command not found: python" because a
  fresh Bash shell has no venv on PATH; reran with source .venv/bin/activate.
- Several Edit calls failed because ruff --fix reformatted docstrings
  (D209) between my Write and Edit; had to re-read/replace by line range.

