## Hints for Future Agents
- The fake mirrors SQLITE semantics on purpose. client_is_sqlite
  (tests/trace/util.py) returns True for it; if you add a
  sqlite-capability gate to a test, it gates the fake too.
- _calls is keyed by call id with NO project scoping on call_end/
  call_update/calls_delete - this matches the SQLite schema (id PRIMARY
  KEY, UPDATE ... WHERE id = ?). Do not "fix" by scoping to project.
- calls_delete counts num_deleted = len(descendants + requested ids) even
  if some requested ids do not exist - SQLite does the same.
- turn_ids in CallsFilter is intentionally IGNORED (SQLite ignores it).
- table rows: digest UNIQUE globally, first writer wins, reads filter by
  project - cross-project same-content rows are invisible to the second
  project, mirroring SQLite.
- obj_create version_index counts ALL rows for (project, object) including
  deleted ones; ON CONFLICT resurrects tombstoned versions in place.
- expire_at stores text; '2100-01-01 00:00:00' default and the computed
  EXPIRE_AT_NEVER isoformat both normalize to None in responses.
- The query evaluator's literal handling: bool literals become 1/0
  (json.dumps renders SQL TRUE/FALSE), dict/list literals compare as
  minified JSON text (real SQLite would be a syntax error; nothing
  exercises it today).
- pytest runs used -p no:randomly for determinism; the suite normally
  randomizes order.
- KNOWN pre-existing local failures (fail at HEAD on sqlite too, verified
  via git stash): tests/flow/test_evaluation_imperative.py
  test_evaluation_invalid_model_name_* (WeaveInitError when run standalone),
  tests/flow/test_scorer.py::test_from_obj_unwraps_nested_weave_object,
